<br>
I have a &quot;Switch&quot; hot key with:<br>
<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet attack<br>
/say Back off and attack %T, %M!!! (just for fun)<br>
<br>
Make sure you have the add targeted, then hit the key a couple times.  One hit from pet, and it will switch.  Back out of melee range, and weigh the options to fight or flee.  <br>
<br>
A good supply of Crystalline Silk Nets and high channeling skill for Gate are also good strategies.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that if you chain-cast a pet, one of the mobs will attack you, especially if you nuked or debuffed them.  Use the Switch key until your pet builds up enough aggro to pull them off of you.  And don't sit down the rest of the fight, else you're going to get beat on again.<br>
<br>
It is a strategy that takes a lot of practice to do without total panic.  Try it on greens first to get comfortable.  I use it for farming Greyhoppers in Marus.  Pull 5 or more, and use Switch so the pet pulls them all off of me, then go out and grab 5 more.  Very useful technique.<br>
<br>
Also, if you are dead-set on gating out, head for the nearest wall, and run at it so that the mob is on the opposite side of it.  Turn towards the mob, then cast.  Basically putting yourself against the wall so that the mob cannot interrupt your casting by moving you.  If you can channel through the bashes, you will make it. <p><div align="center"> <a href="#"><img src="http://www.nemeandesign.net/eq/sig2.jpg" width="382" height="66" border="0" onClick="window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=528641', 'morillion', 'WIDTH=800,HEIGHT=600')"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>See?  Newbies aren't always bad!  </span><br>  Posts: 356<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/03 5:18:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8951.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaPhoto2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage Evasion Techniques?</span><hr size=1> nevermind <p><center><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaSig.gif"><br><font face="garamond" size=4><b>Angel in Devil's Boots<br></font><font size=3 face="garamond"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543802">My Magelo Profile</a></center><font size=0 font face=garamond font color=black></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Drac