which worked for a while, but stopped working when I targetted a different person to assist. I looked at the script and discovered that it changed the &quot;%t&quot; to whoever I targeted the first time I used the hotkey, that is the first line now said &quot;/assist Gronk&quot;, where Gronk was the first person I had the pet assist. I got rid of the &quot;%t&quot; in the command line but that disabled the hotbutton, my pet would chide me that he couldn't do that. How do I do this, or can I?<br>
