<br>
Its a bad idea to bind your pet attack key to your assist key in general. You want the pet attacking and your assisting to be seperate events.<br>
<br>
If you mis-assist or come up with an odd target, the pet will just run off and do whoever knows what. I have a primary assist key that I just put the name of the assist into.<br>
<br>
Slap assist, confirm target visually (glowing name thingo), then pet attack. While its harder to mess up now with the new pet controls, it can still be done. For instance, if the assist happened to have a mob form outside in the corridor in their target, and you hit that key, your pet would charge outside and make life difficult before you realised that you had the wrong target! <p><CENTER><table width=500 border=0 cellspacing=4>
