<br>
<br>
/assist &gt;<br>
/pause 10, 20, 30 (depending on where I am at, don't want to let him loose too soon...)<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
<br>
and for when I get and add on ME, <br>
<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
<br>
that one works well, and can usually get a root out of an earth pet. I often spam that key as I run THROUGH the mob and pet. when I am in a group without an enchanter, I take one /back off and add a /g Pet is tanking add, please pull away from him.<br>
<br>
so that they know that they can pull away, ghetto crowd control, but it works well in Karnors and a few other places where you often get double pulls, especially if you are using a focused 49 water pet, as it tanks fairly well, and the cleric can throw a heal over if needed. For a raid, I have hotkeys for /assist MA, /assist SA, /target Main cleric, /target second cleric. I don't use the /pet attack command on raids, because I never know how long till the puller gets back. It is nice to have pets on raids again, and don't want to mess it up....<br>
